cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper proposes a whole-image CNN regression model for various applications, such as object detection and segmentation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the structure of CNN, which suggests that it may belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The regression model is trained using feature maps, which may also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper demonstrates the method through two tasks, including scene saliency prediction, which may fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
